'''
Explanation for duration missmatch:
- Cal1m, Int1m, METs1m, and Stps1m ("O") contain data for the entire recording duration (max. duration)
    => same data foundation
- HR1m contains less data (why is unknown atp)
- Slp1m and Slp30s ("X") contain only a subset of the recording duration. 
    Hypothesis: subjects took the watch off during the night to charge. Since these files only contain data, 
    when sleep was detected, continuously not wearing the watch during the night either at the beginning or end
    of recording would lead to late/early start and end times 
Note: Duration was calculated as the difference between start and end datetime of the recording file. 
Therefore, missingness or jumps in time (in the cases of slp files) do not affect the duration in this case
'''
